com.intuit.wasabi.tests.library

Class SetupPerformanceTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intuit.wasabi.tests.library.ServiceTestBase
      • com.intuit.wasabi.tests.library.TestBase
        • com.intuit.wasabi.tests.library.SetupPerformanceTest

  • public class SetupPerformanceTest
extends TestBase
    SetupPerformanceTest can be used to setup E experiments for one application, each with B buckets, and each assigned as running on the same page, P. All parameters can be passed in. To pass in new parameters use the -Dparameter-name switches to set the appProperties. The available switches and their default values are: (parametername: defaultvalue)
    • application.name: SW50ZWdyVGVzdA_Application_Perf-
    • experiment.prefix: SW50ZWdyVGVzdA_Experiment_Perf-
    • experiment.count: 3
    • page.name: SW50ZWdyVGVzdA_Page_Perf-
    • bucket.prefix: SW50ZWdyVGVzdA_Bucket_Perf-
    • buckets.in.experiment: 1
    • mutualexclusions: false
    Additionally the parameter mutualexclusions is available. If it is set to true, all experiments are mutual exclusive to each other. By default they are not. NOTE: passing in the string "NULL" for the page name results in that the experiments will not be associated with any page. Priority will automatically be in order of creation, which will be in same order as the experiment names: <experimentPrefix>1 <experimentPrefix>2 ... <experimentPrefix>m Bucket names will be: <bucketPrefix>1 <bucketPrefix>2 ... <bucketPrefix>n Allocation for the buckets will be as follows: With n = bucketCount allocate 1/(n+1) of 100% to each non-control bucket and give the reminder ~ 2/(n+1) of 100% to the control bucket
